<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-13T03:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-13T03:35:00-05:00" n="387" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d387">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">701.9491/21: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-13T12:00:00+03:25">April 13,
                                    1942—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received April 13—9:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>104. Referring to my 103, April 12, Prime Minister last evening informed
                            Japanese Minister that his Legation must depart from Iran within a week.
                            Question of means of exit now under discussion. Japanese wish to proceed
                            to Turkey to which Iranians have no objection. British however do not
                            approve dumping of further Axis diplomats in Turkey and are insisting
                            that Legation return to Japan via Russia.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>